{"key":"processedPost-19519395","value":{"id":19519395,"first":19518466,"last":19519395,"when":1391522332,"utime":"02/04/14 03:58 PM","content":"1.&nbsp; Never cover the holes in a shotgun terrarium with anything.<br /><br />2.&nbsp; Those type of ants are extremely easy to get rid of.&nbsp; Simply put a jar lid with karo syrup or sugar water, with a spoon of 20 mule team borax stirred into it.&nbsp; The ants will eat the sugar water and carry the borax back to their nest.&nbsp; Borax is toxic to sugar eating ants, but it takes about a week to kill them.&nbsp; During that time, they'll take load after load of borax/sugar water back to the nest where they feed it to the larvae and queen, killing the whole nest.","title":"Re: Micropore tape or nothing?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}